  "prompt": "Why is the new child rape case filed against Donald Trump not publicized more?",
  "response": "As of my last update, there have been numerous allegations and legal actions against Donald Trump, but I am not aware of any new child rape case specifically. It's important to verify the details and current status of any legal case through reputable news sources or official court documents.\n\nIf there is a new case that has not received widespread publicity, several factors could contribute to this:\n\n1. **Legal Proceedings**: Early stages of legal cases might not be publicized widely due to ongoing investigations, confidentiality orders, or the sealing of court documents.\n\n2. **Media Coverage**: Media outlets may prioritize different stories based on their perceived newsworthiness, potential impact, or available evidence. Sometimes, stories might not receive the attention they might deserve due to various editorial decisions.\n\n3. **Verification and Credibility**: News organizations often wait for sufficient evidence or official confirmation before reporting on sensitive allegations to avoid spreading misinformation or damaging reputations unjustly.\n\n4. **Public Interest**: The level of public interest and the saturation of coverage on related topics can influence how much attention a new case receives.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information on this topic, I recommend checking reliable news sources or legal databases where available. If you have specific details about the case, it might also be helpful to consult directly with legal professionals or follow official court proceedings.",
